intro: Adenocarpus telonensis var. transiens, commonly known as the Transient Adenocarpus, is a flowering plant native to specific regions of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the Fabaceae family, characterized by its leguminous structure and nitrogen-fixing capabilities. The plant typically features compound leaves and produces small, clustered flowers that are often yellow or green in color. It is adapted to grow in moist, tropical environments, often found in lowland forests or along stream banks. Its botanical significance lies in its ecological role and potential medicinal properties.
